{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":472,"text":"Those of you who have seen the film \"Moneyball,\""},{"time":4167,"text":"or have read the book by Michael Lewis,"},{"time":6151,"text":"will be familiar with the story of Billy Beane."},{"time":9287,"text":"Billy was supposed to be a tremendous ballplayer; all the scouts told him so."},{"time":13975,"text":"They told his parents that"},{"time":15168,"text":"they predicted that he was going to be a star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17207,"text":"But what actually happened when he signed the contract -- and by the way, he didn't"},{"time":22159,"text":"want to sign that contract, he wanted to go to\ncollege --"},{"time":24583,"text":"which is what my mother, who actually does\nlove me,"},{"time":27240,"text":"said that I should do too, and I did --"},{"time":30104,"text":"well, he didn't do very well. He struggled\nmightily."},{"time":33178,"text":"He got traded a couple of times, he ended up in the Minors for most of his career,"},{"time":37711,"text":"and he actually ended up in management. He ended up as a General Manager of the"},{"time":41799,"text":"Oakland A's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42448,"text":"Now for many of you in this room, ending up in management, which is also what I've done,"},{"time":46872,"text":"is seen as a success."},{"time":48568,"text":"I can assure you that for a kid trying to make it in the Bigs,"},{"time":51770,"text":"going into management ain't no success story. It's a failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56479,"text":"And what I want to talk to you about today, and share with you, is that our"},{"time":60918,"text":"healthcare system, our medical system, is\njust as bad at predicting"},{"time":65358,"text":"what happens to people in it -- patients,\nothers --"},{"time":69550,"text":"as those scouts were at predicting what would happen to Billy Beane."},{"time":74163,"text":"And yet, every day"},{"time":76844,"text":"thousands of people in this country"},{"time":78805,"text":"are diagnosed with preconditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82731,"text":"We hear about pre-hypertension, we hear about pre-dementia,"},{"time":86971,"text":"we hear about pre-anxiety, and I'm pretty sure that I diagnosed myself with"},{"time":92307,"text":"that in the green room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93684,"text":"We also refer to subclinical conditions."},{"time":98037,"text":"There's subclinical atherosclerosis, subclinical hardening of the arteries,"},{"time":102588,"text":"obviously linked to heart attacks, potentially."},{"time":106123,"text":"One of my favorites is called\nsubclinical acne."},{"time":109556,"text":"If you look up subclinical acne, you may find a website, which I did,"},{"time":113523,"text":"which says that this is the easiest type of acne to treat."},{"time":117652,"text":"You don't have the pustules or the redness and inflammation."},{"time":124267,"text":"Maybe that's because you don't actually\nhave acne."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127923,"text":"I have a name for all of these conditions, it's another precondition:"},{"time":134446,"text":"I call them preposterous."},{"time":136301,"text":"In baseball, the game follows the pre-game."},{"time":142360,"text":"Season follows the pre-season."},{"time":144765,"text":"But with a lot of these conditions, that actually isn't the case, or at least it isn't the"},{"time":149288,"text":"case all the time. It's as if there's a rain delay, every single time in many cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153861,"text":"We have pre-cancerous lesions,"},{"time":155679,"text":"which often don't turn into cancer."},{"time":159172,"text":"And yet,"},{"time":161028,"text":"if you take, for example, subclinical\nosteoporosis, a bone thinning disease,"},{"time":164954,"text":"the precondition,"},{"time":166607,"text":"otherwise known as osteopenia,"},{"time":169014,"text":"you would have to treat 270\nwomen for three years"},{"time":172684,"text":"in order to prevent one broken bone."},{"time":174884,"text":"That's an awful lot of women"},{"time":176493,"text":"when you multiply by the number of women\nwho were diagnosed"},{"time":179420,"text":"with this osteopenia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181309,"text":"And so is it any wonder,"},{"time":183365,"text":"given all of the costs and the side effects"},{"time":185895,"text":"of the drugs that we're using to treat these preconditions, that every year"},{"time":190099,"text":"we're spending more than two trillion dollars on healthcare and yet"},{"time":193772,"text":"100,000 people a year -- and that's a conservative estimate -- are dying"},{"time":197059,"text":"not because of the conditions they have,"},{"time":198972,"text":"but because of the treatments that we're giving them and the complications of those treatments?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203259,"text":"We've medicalized everything"},{"time":206071,"text":"in this country."},{"time":207040,"text":"Women in the audience, I have\nsome"},{"time":210423,"text":"pretty bad news that you already know,"},{"time":212422,"text":"and that's that every aspect of your\nlife"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215079,"text":"has been medicalized."},{"time":216487,"text":"Strike one is when you hit puberty."},{"time":218911,"text":"You now have something that happens to you once a month that has been medicalized."},{"time":223247,"text":"It's a condition;"},{"time":224063,"text":"it has to be treated. Strike two"},{"time":225623,"text":"is if you get pregnant."},{"time":227223,"text":"That's been medicalized as\nwell."},{"time":230319,"text":"You have to have a high-tech experience"},{"time":232239,"text":"of pregnancy, otherwise something might go wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234967,"text":"Strike three is menopause."},{"time":238574,"text":"We all know what happened when millions of women were given hormone replacement therapy"},{"time":242911,"text":"for menopausal symptoms"},{"time":245957,"text":"for decades until all of a sudden we realized, because a study came out, a big one,"},{"time":250387,"text":"NIH-funded."},{"time":251395,"text":"It said,"},{"time":252323,"text":"actually, a lot of that hormone replacement therapy may be doing more harm than good"},{"time":256908,"text":"for many of those women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258692,"text":"Just in case,"},{"time":260940,"text":"I don't want to leave the men out --"},{"time":262572,"text":"I am one, after all --"},{"time":264188,"text":"I have really bad news for all of you in\nthis room,"},{"time":266877,"text":"and for everyone"},{"time":267837,"text":"listening and watching elsewhere:"},{"time":269583,"text":"You all have"},{"time":270796,"text":"a universally fatal condition."},{"time":273732,"text":"So, just take a moment."},{"time":277040,"text":"It's called pre-death."},{"time":278372,"text":"Every single one of you has it, because\nyou have the risk factor for it,"},{"time":283444,"text":"which is being alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285188,"text":"But I have some good news for you,\nbecause"},{"time":288246,"text":"I'm a journalist, I like to end things in a happy way or a forward-thinking way."},{"time":292276,"text":"And that good news is that if you can survive to the end of my talk, which"},{"time":296205,"text":"we'll see if that happens for everyone,"},{"time":298797,"text":"you will be a pre-vivor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302092,"text":"I made up pre-death."},{"time":306908,"text":"If I used someone else's pre-death, I apologize,"},{"time":311020,"text":"I think I made it up."},{"time":312605,"text":"I didn't make up pre-vivor."},{"time":314172,"text":"Pre-vivor is what a particular cancer advocacy group would like everyone who"},{"time":319644,"text":"just has a risk factor,"},{"time":320916,"text":"but hasn't actually had that cancer,"},{"time":323438,"text":"to call themselves."},{"time":324812,"text":"You are a pre-vivor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326387,"text":"We've had HBO here this morning. I'm wondering if Mark Burnett is anywhere in the"},{"time":330860,"text":"audience, I'd like to suggest"},{"time":332365,"text":"a reality TV show called \"Pre-vivor.\""},{"time":336572,"text":"If you develop a disease, you're off\nthe island."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340073,"text":"But the problem is, we have a system"},{"time":345208,"text":"that is completely --"},{"time":347080,"text":"basically promoted this."},{"time":349007,"text":"We've selected, at every point in this system,"},{"time":351873,"text":"to do what we do, and to give everyone a\nprecondition and then eventually"},{"time":355860,"text":"a condition, in some cases."},{"time":357839,"text":"Start with the doctor-patient\nrelationship. Doctors, most of them,"},{"time":362332,"text":"are in a fee-for-service system. They are\nbasically incentivized to do more --"},{"time":367358,"text":"procedures, tests,"},{"time":369015,"text":"prescribe medications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370681,"text":"Patients come to them,"},{"time":372046,"text":"they want to do something. We're\nAmericans, we can't just stand"},{"time":376046,"text":"there, we have to do something. And so\nthey want a drug."},{"time":378927,"text":"They want a treatment. They want to be told, this is what you have and this is how"},{"time":382702,"text":"you treat it. If the doctor\ndoesn't give you that,"},{"time":385022,"text":"you go somewhere else."},{"time":386846,"text":"That's not very good for doctors'\nbusiness."},{"time":388726,"text":"Or even worse,"},{"time":390414,"text":"if you are diagnosed with something\neventually, and the doctor didn't order that test,"},{"time":394373,"text":"you get sued."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396597,"text":"We have pharmaceutical companies that are\nconstantly trying to expand"},{"time":399629,"text":"the indications, expand the number of people who are eligible for a given treatment,"},{"time":404973,"text":"because that obviously helps their bottom line.\nWe have advocacy groups,"},{"time":407766,"text":"like the one that's come up with\npre-vivor,"},{"time":410021,"text":"who want to make more and more people feel they are at risk, or might have a condition,"},{"time":414261,"text":"so that they can raise more funds"},{"time":416390,"text":"and raise visibility, et cetera."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419005,"text":"But this isn't actually,"},{"time":420845,"text":"despite what journalists typically do,\nthis isn't actually about blaming"},{"time":423941,"text":"particular players."},{"time":425229,"text":"We are all responsible."},{"time":427030,"text":"I'm responsible."},{"time":428472,"text":"I actually root for the Yankees, I mean talk\nabout"},{"time":431510,"text":"rooting for the worst\npossible"},{"time":434702,"text":"offender when it comes to doing\neverything you can do."},{"time":437312,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":438849,"text":"But everyone is responsible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442813,"text":"I went to medical school,"},{"time":445718,"text":"and I didn't have a course called How to Think Skeptically,"},{"time":450470,"text":"or How Not to Order Tests."},{"time":452133,"text":"We have this system"},{"time":454784,"text":"where that's what you do."},{"time":457301,"text":"And it actually took being a journalist"},{"time":459926,"text":"to understand all these incentives. You know, economists like to say,"},{"time":463829,"text":"there are no bad people,"},{"time":465048,"text":"there are just bad incentives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466925,"text":"And that's actually true."},{"time":468533,"text":"Because what we've created is a sort of Field of Dreams, when it comes to medical technology."},{"time":472000,"text":"So when you put another MRI in\nevery corner, you put a robot"},{"time":477300,"text":"in every hospital saying that everyone has to have robotic surgery."},{"time":480838,"text":"Well, we've created a system where if you\nbuild it, they will come."},{"time":484654,"text":"But you can actually perversely"},{"time":488181,"text":"tell people to come, convince them"},{"time":490965,"text":"that they have to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492654,"text":"It was when I became a journalist that I really realized how I was part of this problem,"},{"time":497462,"text":"and how we all are part of this problem."},{"time":499486,"text":"I was medicalizing every risk factor, I was writing stories, commissioning stories,"},{"time":503142,"text":"every day, that were trying to,"},{"time":506535,"text":"not necessarily make people worried, although that was what often happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509532,"text":"But, you know, there are ways out."},{"time":512555,"text":"I saw my own internist last week,"},{"time":514427,"text":"and he said to me,"},{"time":516959,"text":"\"You know,\" and he told me something that"},{"time":519476,"text":"everyone in this audience could have\ntold me for free,"},{"time":521950,"text":"but I paid him for the privilege, which\nis that"},{"time":524438,"text":"I need to lose some weight."},{"time":526107,"text":"Well, he's right. I've had honest-to-goodness high blood pressure"},{"time":530564,"text":"for a dozen years now, same"},{"time":532277,"text":"age my father got it,"},{"time":534051,"text":"and it's a real disease. It's not pre-hypertension, it's actual"},{"time":537838,"text":"hypertension, high blood pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539811,"text":"Well, he's right,"},{"time":540796,"text":"but he didn't say to me,"},{"time":543876,"text":"well, you have pre-obesity or"},{"time":545563,"text":"you have pre-diabetes, or anything like that. He didn't say,"},{"time":548908,"text":"better start taking this Statin, you need to lower your cholesterol."},{"time":552284,"text":"No, he said, \"Go out and lose some weight. Come back and see me in a bit,"},{"time":555443,"text":"or just give me a call and let me know how you're doing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":557444,"text":"So that's, to me,"},{"time":559484,"text":"a way forward."},{"time":561115,"text":"Billy Beane, by the way, learned the same\nthing."},{"time":563479,"text":"He learned,"},{"time":565015,"text":"from watching this kid who he eventually hired, who was really successful for him,"},{"time":568532,"text":"that it wasn't swinging for the fences, it\nwasn't swinging at every pitch"},{"time":573407,"text":"like the sluggers do, which is what all the expensive teams like the Yankees like to --"},{"time":578176,"text":"they like to pick up those guys."},{"time":579516,"text":"This kid told him, you know, you gotta watch the guys, and you gotta go out and find"},{"time":584105,"text":"the guys who like to walk,"},{"time":585344,"text":"because getting on base by a walk"},{"time":587048,"text":"is just as good, and in our healthcare\nsystem"},{"time":589816,"text":"we need to figure out,"},{"time":591256,"text":"is that really a good pitch"},{"time":592832,"text":"or should we let it go by and not swing at everything?"},{"time":595750,"text":"Thanks."}]}]}